        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "The 'search the manual' function of the documentation is absolutely useless, failing to return any results for many search terms which should clearly be there, and returning useless results for many others.  Not having content list at the top of the manual pages exacerbates this.  Some examples:\n\nSuppose I want to look at the docs for partial view helper:\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/search?query=partial&language=en&search=Search+Manual!\n(1 result; 24.3. Using the Book Search Data API)\n\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/search?query=partial+view+helper&language=en&search=Search+Manual!\n(4 pages of results; although one of the early ones is for the view helper page, as there is no content list at the top of the page, the only way from there is to search the page until you find what you want.\n\nSuppose I want to look at the docs for the EmailAddress validator:\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/search?query=EmailAddress&language=en&search=Search+Manual!\nNo results.\n\n\nIt would be better just to use Google site search; it's at least a quick fix that would make it usable.\n"
        },
