        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32265",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You're reporting two very distinct and separate issues: (1) you feel the search does not return sufficient results, and (2) individual manual pages do not have a TOC.\n\n(2) is a limitation of DocBook -> HTML rendering. There may be a way to allow it, but I'm not going to make it a priority for the team based on this single complaint.\n\n(1) is likely a Zend_Search_Lucene issue (as we use Z_S_L to index the manual as well as to search that index). However, that said, I'd like a list of search terms you've encountered that do not return results so that we can test.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-29T05:04:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-29T05:04:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32267",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lightflowmark",
                        "name": "lightflowmark",
                        "displayName": "Mark",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fair point; if the search linked to the correct anchor in the page, then the T.O.C. would be a trivial issue at best.  I don't know if Z_S_L can do this or not.\n\nI'll add comments to this issue as I come across search terms that give what I feel are incomplete \/ inaccurate results.  I've had this problem for months and finally got frustrated enough to file an issue :-)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lightflowmark",
                        "name": "lightflowmark",
                        "displayName": "Mark",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-29T05:39:51.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-29T05:39:51.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32291",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lightflowmark",
                        "name": "lightflowmark",
                        "displayName": "Mark",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Part of the problem is that the search results page doesn't return any context for the links, and with the long manual pages, this can be confusing.\n\nFor instance, I want information on using the context parameter of the Zend_Form validators:\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/search?query=validator+context&language=en&search=Search+Manual!\nThe relevant page is actually second on the list, '23.3. Creating Form Elements Using Zend_Form_Element [en]', but it's far from obvious from the title alone that this is a relevant result (there are 2 pages of results for this query).  Adding a few lines of context a la Google would make the search much more useful:\nhttp:\/\/www.google.co.uk\/search?q=site:framework.zend.com+validator+context\n\nEven though the correct result is further down the list, it's easier to locate.\n\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lightflowmark",
                        "name": "lightflowmark",
                        "displayName": "Mark",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-30T00:51:51.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-30T00:51:51.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32316",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lightflowmark",
                        "name": "lightflowmark",
                        "displayName": "Mark",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Headscript - no results:\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/search?query=headscript&language=en&search=Search+Manual!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lightflowmark",
                        "name": "lightflowmark",
                        "displayName": "Mark",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-01T05:05:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-01T05:05:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32375",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lightflowmark",
                        "name": "lightflowmark",
                        "displayName": "Mark",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "htmltag - no results\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/search?query=htmltag&language=en&search=Search+Manual!\nI'll keep posting these until you tell me you've got enough.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lightflowmark",
                        "name": "lightflowmark",
                        "displayName": "Mark",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-03T04:55:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-03T04:55:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32379",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm not surprised that searching on \"headscript\" and \"htmltag\" are returning no results -- as they are stubs of full class names. In these particular cases, I'd say that Lucene is doing the correct thing-- there are no tokens generated for the words you're searching for as they don't exist as distinct words anywhere in the manual pages.\n\nTry searching on Zend_View_Helper_HeadScript and Zend_View_Helper_HtmlTag -- these return plenty of results.\n\nRegarding the idea of including context, that may be possible for us to do, and I'll look into it.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-03T08:52:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-03T08:52:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32383",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lightflowmark",
                        "name": "lightflowmark",
                        "displayName": "Mark",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fair enough - I know almost nothing about Lucene, but I'm still surprised that the 'headscript' search fails - the word appears a half-dozen times on the page as a distinct word, as a section heading '60.4.1.8. HeadScript Helper', link, and in other text.  \n\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.view.helpers.html\n\nAnyway, the context should really help - thanks.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lightflowmark",
                        "name": "lightflowmark",
                        "displayName": "Mark",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-03T15:02:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-03T15:02:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37025",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Matthew: I implemented Lucene for my own version of documentation:\r\nHeadscript returns me less page than Zend_View_Helper_HeadScript but it returns me some results:\r\nhttp:\/\/www.mikaelkael.fr\/doczf\/search.php?zf_version=1.9&lang=de&query_search=Headscript\r\nhttp:\/\/www.mikaelkael.fr\/doczf\/search.php?lang=en&zf_version=1.9&query_search=Zend_View_Helper_HeadScript\r\n\r\nTo generate TOC in each page (TOC of the section, not the one of the chapter), you have to parameterize: html.xsl.in with addition of <xsl:param name=\"generate.section.toc.level\" select=\"1\"><\/xsl:param>\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
                        "name": "mikaelkael",
                        "displayName": "Mickael Perraud",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-18T02:54:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-18T02:54:31.000+0000"
                },
